<inglise> COMMISSION REGULATION (EC) No 770/96 of 26 April 1996 amending Regulation (EEC) No 3002/92 laying down common detailed rules for verifying the use and/or destination of products from intervention </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (EM&Uuml;) nr 770/96 sekkumisvarudest p&auml;rit toodete kasutamise ja/v&otilde;i sihtkoha kontrollimise &uuml;ksikasjalikke &uuml;hiseeskirju kehtestava m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 3002/92 muutmise kohta 26. aprill 1996 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation No 136/66/EEC of 22 September 1966 on the establishment of a common organization of the market in oils and fats (1), as last amended by Regulation (EC) No 3290/94 (2), and in particular Articles 12 (4) and 26 (3) thereof, and to the corresponding provisions of the other Regulations establishing a common organization of agricultural product markets, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 22. septembri 1966. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust nr 136/66/EM&Uuml; &otilde;li- ja rasvaturu &uuml;hise korralduse kehtestamise kohta (1) (viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;) nr 3290/94 (2)), eriti selle artikli 12 l&otilde;iget 4 ja artikli 26 l&otilde;iget 3, ning muude p&otilde;llumajandustoodete &uuml;hist turukorraldust k&auml;sitlevate m&auml;&auml;ruste vastavaid s&auml;tteid ning arvestades, et </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Commission Regulation (EEC) No 3002/92 (3), as last amended by Regulation (EEC) No 1938/93 (4), lays down common detailed rules notably as to the release of the security which guarantees the proper use and/or destination of products from intervention; </inglise>
<eesti> komisjoni m&auml;&auml;rus (EM&Uuml;) nr 3002/92 (3) (viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 1938/93 (4)) s&auml;testab &uuml;ksikasjalikud &uuml;hiseeskirjad eelk&otilde;ige sekkumisvarudest p&auml;rit toodete sihip&auml;rase kasutamise ja /v&otilde;i sihtkoha tagamiseks antud tagatise vabastamise kohta; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Article 8 (1) of Council Regulation (EEC) No 729/70 (5) of 21 April 1970 on the financing of the common agricultural policy, as last amended by Regulation (EC) No 1287/95 (6), requires Member States to take the measures necessary to recover sums lost as a result of irregularities in accordance with national provisions laid down by law, regulation or administrative action; </inglise>
<eesti> &uuml;hise p&otilde;llumajanduspoliitika rahastamist k&auml;sitleva n&otilde;ukogu 21. aprilli 1970. aasta m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 729/70 (5) (viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;) nr 1287/95 (6)) artikli 8 l&otilde;ikes 1 n&otilde;utakse liikmesriikidelt, et nad v&otilde;taksid vajalikke meetmeid eeskirjade eiramise v&otilde;i hooletuse tagaj&auml;rjel kaotatud summade sissen&otilde;udmiseks vastavalt siseriiklikele &otilde;igusnormidele; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas in order to ensure equal treatment of sales from intervention stocks at a reduced price level and comparable schemes which provide for the granting of an aid, notably export refunds, to ensure equal treatment for operators in the Member States and to facilitate the recovery of economic advantages unduly granted it is appropriate to provide for the payment of an amount equal to the amount of the security unduly released; </inglise>
<eesti> sekkumisvarudest p&auml;rit alandatud hindadega m&uuml;&uuml;gi ja vastavate toetuse andmist eelk&otilde;ige eksporditoetustena etten&auml;gevate s&uuml;steemide v&otilde;rdse kohtlemise tagamiseks ning liikmesriikide ettev&otilde;tjate v&otilde;rdse kohtlemise tagamiseks ning p&otilde;hjendamatult saadud majandusliku kasu sissen&otilde;udmise h&otilde;lbustamiseks on vaja ette n&auml;ha, et tuleb maksta p&otilde;hjendamatult vabastatud tagatisega v&otilde;rdne summa; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the relevant management committees, </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses s&auml;testatud meetmed on koosk&otilde;las asjaomaste korralduskomiteede arvamusega, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> The following Article is inserted in Regulation (EEC) No 3002/92: </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;rusele (EM&Uuml;) nr 3002/92 lisatakse j&auml;rgmine artikkel: </eesti>
<inglise> 'Article 5a </inglise>
<eesti> "Artikkel 5a </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Where, after the release in whole or in part of the security referred to in Article 5, it is established that the products in whole or in part did not reach the prescribed use and/or destination the competent authority of the Member State where the security has been released shall require, in accordance with Article 8 (1) of Regulation (EEC) No 729/70, the operator concerned to pay an amount equal to the amount of the security which would have been forfeited if the failure would have been taken into account before the release of the security. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui p&auml;rast artiklis 5 nimetatud tagatise t&auml;ielikku v&otilde;i osalist vabastamist tehakse kindlaks, et kogu kaup v&otilde;i osa sellest ei j&otilde;udnud etten&auml;htud kasutusse ja/ v&otilde;i sihtkohta, n&otilde;uab tagatise vabastanud liikmesriigi p&auml;dev asutus vastavalt m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 729/70 artikli 8 l&otilde;ikele 1, et asjaomane ettev&otilde;tja maksaks summa, mis on v&otilde;rdne tagatisega, millest oleks ilma j&auml;&auml;dud, kui eeskirjade eiramist v&otilde;i hooletust oleks arvesse v&otilde;etud enne tagatise vabastamist. </eesti>
<inglise> This amount shall be increased by interest calculated from the date of release to the day preceding the date of payment. </inglise>
<eesti> Sellele summale lisatakse alates tagatise vabastamise kuup&auml;evast kuni maksmisele eelneva kuup&auml;evani arvestatud intress. </eesti>
<inglise> The receipt by the competent authority of the amount referred to in the preceding subparagraph shall constitute the recovery of the economic advantage unduly granted. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui p&auml;dev asutus v&otilde;tab vastu eelmises l&otilde;igus nimetatud summa, loetakse see p&otilde;hjendamatult saadud majandusliku kasu sissen&otilde;udmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The payment shall be made within 30 days from the day of receipt of the demand for payment. </inglise>
<eesti> Makse tuleb sooritada 30 p&auml;eva jooksul alates maksen&otilde;ude k&auml;ttesaamisest. </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the time limit for payment is not met, Member States may decide that, instead of payment, the amount to be received shall be deducted from subsequent payments to the operator concerned. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui makset&auml;htajast kinni ei peeta, v&otilde;ib liikmesriik otsustada, et makse asemel peetakse saamata summa kinni k&otilde;nealusele ettev&otilde;tjale tehtavatest j&auml;rgnevatest maksetest. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> The interest rate shall be calculated in accordance with the provisions of national law but may not be less than the rate applicable for the recovery of national amounts. </inglise>
<eesti> Intressim&auml;&auml;r arvutatakse vastavalt siseriiklikele &otilde;igusaktidele, kuid see ei tohi olla madalam kui siseriiklike v&auml;ljamaksete sissen&otilde;udmisel kehtiv intressim&auml;&auml;r. </eesti>
<inglise> No interest shall be levied, or at the most an amount to be determined by the Member State corresponding to the undue profit, if the release of the security was an error of the competent authority. </inglise>
<eesti> P&auml;deva asutuse vea t&otilde;ttu p&otilde;hjendamatult vabastatud tagatiselt intressi ei n&otilde;uta v&otilde;i n&otilde;utakse k&otilde;ige enam alusetult saadud tulu suurusele vastav summa, mille m&auml;&auml;rab kindlaks liikmesriik. </eesti>
<inglise> 4. </inglise>
<eesti> 4. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States may refrain from demanding the payment referred to in paragraph 1 where the amount does not exceed ECU 60, provided that, under national law, such cases are covered by similar rules. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid v&otilde;ivad mitte n&otilde;uda l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud makse tegemist, kui summa ei &uuml;leta 60 ek&uuml;&uuml;d ja kui siseriiklike &otilde;igusaktide kohaselt kehtib niisugusel puhul sama reegel. </eesti>
<inglise> 5. </inglise>
<eesti> 5. </eesti>
<inglise> The amount received in accordance with paragraph 1 shall be paid to the paying agency which shall deduct the amounts concerned from the European Agricultural Guidance and Guarantee Fund (EAGGF) expenditure, without prejudice to Article 7 of Council Regulation (EEC) No 595/91 (*). </inglise>
<eesti> L&otilde;ike 1 alusel vastuv&otilde;etud summa makstakse makseasutustele, mis arvab k&otilde;nealused summad maha Euroopa P&otilde;llumajanduse Arendus- ja Tagatisfondi (EAGGFi) kuludest, ilma et see piiraks n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 595/91 artikli 7 kohaldamist. </eesti>
<inglise> (*) OJ No L 67, 14.3.1991, p. 11. </inglise>
<eesti> * E&Uuml;T L 67, 14.03.1991, lk 11." </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the seventh day following its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub seitsmendal p&auml;eval p&auml;rast selle avaldamist Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas. </eesti>
<inglise> It shall apply to securities given on or after that date. </inglise>
<eesti> Seda kohaldatakse sel p&auml;eval v&otilde;i edaspidi esitatud tagatiste suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 26 April 1996. </inglise>
